    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <head>171. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_NRM1" type="from"
                        >Nixon</persName> to Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RWP1"
                        type="to">Rogers</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d171fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, White House
                        Special Files, President’s Office Files, Chronological File,
                        1/1/72–12/21/72. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1972-08-22">August 22, 1972</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Determination and Authorization of the Grant to the Kingdom of Thailand of
                        up<lb/>to $50 Million in Defense Articles and Services in <gloss
                            target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1973</item>
                </list>
                <p>In accordance with the recommendation in your memorandum of July 12,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d171fn2">Not found.</note> I hereby: <list>
                        <label>A.</label>
                        <item>Determine, pursuant to Section 614(a) of the Foreign Assistance Act of
                            1961, as amended, (22 <gloss target="#t_USC1">U.S.C.</gloss> 2364), that
                            the use of up to $50 million of funds available in <gloss
                                target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1973 for the grant of defense articles
                            and services, including excess defense articles, to Thailand, without
                            regard to the requirement of Section 514 of the Act, is important to the
                            security of the United States; and</item>
                        <label>B.</label>
                        <item>Authorize, pursuant to Section 614(a) of the Act, such use of up to
                            $50 million of funds for the grant of defense articles and services,
                            including excess defense articles, to Thailand, without regard to the
                            requirements of Section 514 of the Act.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0421" n="372" xml:id="pg_372"/>
                <p>You are requested on my behalf to notify the Speaker of the House of
                    Representatives and the Senate Foreign Relations Committee of my intention to
                    take this action, in accordance with Section 652 of the Foreign Assistance Act
                    of 1961, as amended, and to specify an effective date for this
                    determination.</p>
                <p>This determination shall be classified SECRET and shall not be published in the
                        <hi rend="italic">Federal Register</hi>. Such publication would be harmful
                    to the security of the United States because it could jeopardize continuing use
                    by the United States of Royal Thai Air Force bases by raising the issue of the
                    nature of our defense relationship with Thailand.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Richard Nixon</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
